                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 [Chase, Augustus S.]: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 18, 1946—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Text your telegram has been repeated Chungking with Dept’s approval in
                    principle (Urtel 26, Apr 15) but with final authority resting with General
                    Marshall.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
